Activity:

1) Create a google document and add the following:
2) Create a semi-detailed outline about JS Control Structures
3) Assumptions:
 Audience: People with no background in JS, but knows HTML and CSS
 Duration: 1 Hour


I. Getting to know JavaScript
     A. What is JavaScript?
     B. Why do we have to use it?
     C. Why is it important?
     D. Open code editor
     E. create file app.js


II. Control structures
     A. Meet Control Statements
          1. What are Control Statements?
          2. Why do we need it?
    
     B. Using Control Statements
        B.1. What do I need to know before using it?
          1. What are datatypes and variables?
          2. What are comparison or conditional expressions?
          3. What are mathematical operators?
          4. What is console.log()?
          
        B.2. Types of Control Statements
          1. Conditional Control Statements
              A. If - else statements
                                      var money = 5;

                                      if (money >= 10) {
                                        console.log("You can buy a big ice cream!");
                                      } else {
                                        console.log("You can buy a small ice cream.");
                                      }
                                      
                                      
                                      
                                      
              B. Switch case
                                      var number = 2;
                                      var fruit;

                                      switch (number) {
                                        case 1:
                                          fruit = "Apple";
                                          break;
                                        case 2:
                                          fruit = "Banana";
                                          break;
                                        case 3:
                                          fruit = "Orange";
                                          break;
                                        default:
                                          fruit = "Unknown fruit";
                                      }

                                      console.log("You chose a " + fruit + "!");
          
       2. Looping/Iterative control statements
             A. While loop
                                      var i = 1;

                                      while (i <= 5) {
                                        console.log(i);
                                        i++;
                                      }
                                      
                                      
                                      
             B. For loop
                                      for (var i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
                                         console.log(i);  
                                      }
                                      
                                      
                                      
             C. doWhile loop
                                     var i = 1;

                                     do {
                                       console.log(i);
                                       i++;
                                     } while (i <= 5);
                                     
                                     
                                     
             D. For ...inloop
                                    var basket = {
                                       apple: 3,
                                       banana: 2,
                                       orange: 4
                                     };

                                     for (var fruit in basket) {
                                       console.log(fruit);
                                     };
                                     
                                     
                                     
        3. Break statement
                                     for (var i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
                                        if (i === 6) {
                                          break;
                                        }
                                        console.log(i);
                                      };
                                      
                                      
                                      
        4. Continue statement
                                     for (var i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
                                        if (i % 2 === 0) {
                                          continue;
                                        }
                                        console.log(i);
                                      }
